KHARTOUM, March 21 (Xinhua) -- Sudan on Monday condemned Yemen's Houthi militia for its attacks on civilian and oil facilities in Saudi Arabia, according to Sudan's Foreign Ministry's statement. Sudan called for a wide regional and international alignment to face the Houthi's threat to the region, the statement said. The Houthis on Sunday reportedly launched missiles and drones toward economic and civilian facilities in several regions south of Saudi Arabia.  â– 